D.Styles &amp; Meve
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC0192AA6C7178A9CB8" bold="true" box="[591,677,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="719A274EFFDEFFC0192AA6C7178A9CB8" box="[591,677,1172,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C0E65AA2FFDEFFC019D0A6C7162D9CB8" box="[693,770,1172,1198]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[211,1377,208,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-32@3.[192,1396,187,1925]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ceropegia heidukiae from Ngome, KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa. A, Full habit; B, Lateral view of flower; C, Fully-grown, nearly mature follicles; D, E, Close up of corolla lobes showing colour variation; F, Close lateral view of tooth-like protrusions at petal sinuses; G, Grassland habitat at Ngome. Photographs: David Styles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423780" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423780/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="C0E65AA2FFDEFFC0185CA6C716679CB8" box="[825,840,1172,1198]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[203,1393,202,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[192,1396,190,1928]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Morphological details of Ceropegia heidukiae flowers.A, Longitudinal section through corolla showing the inner colouration; B, Bract; C, Lateral view of gynostegium and corona (short stipe not visible); D, Top view of gynostegium; E, Pollinarium; F, Cluster of fleshy fusiform roots. Photographs: David Styles (A, B, F) and Annemarie Heiduk (C–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423784" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423784/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">2</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58624627FFDEFFC01BEDA6B311819DDB" blockId="1.[136,1452,1248,1558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC01B8BA6B314859CE3" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[238,426,1248,1269]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudatisii">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC01B8BA6B314859CE3" box="[238,426,1248,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">Ceropegia rudatisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a subset of vegetative and floral characters such as a cluster of fleshy fusiform roots, erect stems, short petiolate, ovate and glabrous leaves, small lanceolate sepals and longitudinally ribbed corolla tubes with unfused corolla lobe tips, and overall structure of the corona. The flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC019D5A77B16059D2B" authorityName="D. Styles &amp; Meve" authorityYear="2021" box="[688,810,1320,1341]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heidukiae">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC019D5A77B16059D2B" box="[688,810,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">C. heidukiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC018C6A77B113E9D2B" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[931,1041,1320,1341]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudatisii">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC018C6A77B113E9D2B" box="[931,1041,1320,1341]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">C. rudatisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having much longer bracts (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01E21A77B10A69D2B" box="[1348,1417,1320,1342]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01BD8A71F14219D77" box="[189,270,1356,1377]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC01A55A71F14B19D77" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[304,414,1356,1377]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudatisii">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC01A55A71F14B19D77" box="[304,414,1356,1377]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">C. rudatisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), shorter pedicels (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC0193EA71F17969D77" box="[603,697,1356,1377]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="7.0">7–21 mm</quantity>
vs. up to 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01878A71F164A9D77" box="[797,869,1356,1378]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="53.0">53 mm</quantity>
), shorter total length (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01F58A71F11889D77" box="[1085,1191,1356,1378]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="57.5" valueMax="65.0" valueMin="50.0">50–65 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01FB7A71F10119D77" box="[1234,1342,1356,1378]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.1" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="71.0" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="57.0">57–85 mm</quantity>
), a broader corolla tube (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01A5BA72314E49D93" box="[318,459,1392,1414]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.45" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="14.5" valueMin="10.5">10.5–14.5 mm</quantity>
wide at mouth vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC019E2A72317F49D93" box="[647,731,1392,1414]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
), shorter spreading corolla lobes (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01F41A723119E9D93" box="[1060,1201,1392,1414]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.85" metricValueMin="1.35" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="18.5" valueMin="13.5">13.5–18.5 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01FBEA72310469D93" box="[1243,1385,1392,1414]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" metricValueMax="3.45" metricValueMin="2.75" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="31.0" valueMax="34.5" valueMin="27.5">27.5–34.5 mm</quantity>
) being broad ovate (vs. narrow lanceolate), strongly projecting (tooth-like) sinuses at base of corolla lobes (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC01F89A7C710769DBF" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[1260,1369,1428,1449]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudatisii">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC01F89A7C710769DBF" box="[1260,1369,1428,1449]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">C. rudatisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), longer staminal corona lobes (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01AF9A7EB14FB9DDB" box="[412,468,1464,1485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01A9EA7EB17619DDB" box="[507,590,1464,1485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
), and shorter seed coma (
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC01827A7EB16A99DDB" box="[834,902,1464,1486]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="45.0">45 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="9F25EBC2FFDEFFC018C8A7EB113B9DDB" box="[941,1044,1464,1486]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="52.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="50.0">50–55 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName id="9FDD3DA4FFDEFFC01F56A7EB118F9DDB" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityYear="1907" box="[1075,1184,1464,1485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Ceropegia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rudatisii">
<emphasis id="6AA99A35FFDEFFC01F56A7EB118F9DDB" box="[1075,1184,1464,1485]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="21">C. rudatisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
